# What `gcloud builds submit ../pipeline` UPLOADS (infra/10-deploy-pipeline.sh).
#
# This file is the only thing that trims the upload. gcloud ignores .dockerignore
# here, and it auto-generates rules from .gitignore only when one sits in the
# source directory — ours is at the repo root, which gcloud never looks at. With
# no .gcloudignore, every deploy shipped 301 MiB / ~11.5k files, ~240MB of it the
# local .venv. (.dockerignore still governs the docker build context inside Cloud
# Build, so both files are needed and their contents overlap.)
#
# The image only ever COPYs pyproject.toml and app/ — see Dockerfile.
.gcloudignore
.git/
.gitignore

# The local uv virtualenv: the bulk of the upload, built against the host's
# interpreter, and never used by the image (it installs with `uv pip install --system`).
.venv/
uv.lock

tests/
.env
__pycache__/
*.pyc
.pytest_cache/
*.egg-info/
